data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The signature changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Action<...>`, so manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` code won't compile — but also isn't needed anymore.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get disambiguated column names (e.g., `Street1`). A migration will be generated to rename columns.

**b) Nested complex types use full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix both** by pinning column names explicitly with `HasColumnName()`:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

This preserves your existing schema and avoids a column-rename migration.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Update your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    {
        // Use logCommandText for safe logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface — they all gained this parameter.
